  "response_text": "A tub of Smart Balance Buttery Spread sits alone on a rugged, tan, rock-like surface, centered against a vivid studio background that fades from pink near the horizon to bright blue above. The product is small at first, perched on the highest slab like a display pedestal. As the view moves closer, the yellow tub with a white lid fills more of the scene. The large black words “SMART BALANCE” become clearer on the front label, with red and green bands above it. The upper label includes health-related text, including “Patented blend to help improve cholesterol ratio,” and a red band that refers to no trans fatty acids and no hydrogenated oil.\n\nThe product image gives way to a simple medical-style bar chart over a muted, textured background. A vertical scale on the left is marked 50, 100, 150, and 200. Three bars are labeled along the bottom: “Total Cholesterol,” “LDL ‘Bad,’” and “HDL ‘Good.’” The total cholesterol bar is tallest, near 200; the LDL bar is lower, around the middle; and the HDL bar is shorter, around 100. Small fine print runs along the bottom explaining that total cholesterol is composed of HDL and LDL, with a small additional amount of VLDL.\n\nThe chart fades into food imagery. A square white bowl of bright green cut beans sits on a pale gray surface. Small reddish flecks are scattered among the beans. A soft yellow dollop of buttery spread appears on top of the beans, resting near the center and standing out against the green.\n\nThe scene changes to a warm, brown serving bowl filled with a chunky orange-brown baked dish or casserole. A pale yellow dollop of spread sits on top. From the right, a hand uses a metal serving spoon to lift a portion from the bowl. The spoon carries the serving across to a yellow plate on the right, where a lemon slice and a small green garnish are already arranged. The portion lands on the plate with some of the spread visible on top, suggesting it is being served as part of the dish.\n\nNext is a pla